examples: Nomic is a metagame in which players can modify the rules as part of gameplay.

definitions.definition: The exploitation of the rules etc. of some other game, at a higher level than simply playing the game normally; a game outside or peripheral to the actual gameplay .

secondary_definitions: ( countable , uncountable ) The exploitation of the rules etc. of some other game, at a higher level than simply playing the game normally; a game outside or peripheral to the actual gameplay .
